    english: "<h2>Mahakaleshwar Jyotirlinga's History</h2>:-->Mahakaleshwar Jyotirlinga is located in the city of Ujjain in the state of Madhya Pradesh,India.It is one of the 12 Jyotirlingas and is considered one of the most sacred.Mahakal means the Lord of Time and Death,i.e.,Lord Shiva.According to thePuranas,there was a king named Chandrasena in Ujjain who was a devotee of Lord Shiva. A demon named Dushan, who had received boons from Brahma, attacked Ujjain and started troubling theShiva devotees.Chandrasena and other devotees prayed to Lord Shiva, who appeared andkilled the demon.The Mahakaleshwar temple is famous for its Bhasma Aarti (aritual performed with ashes) at dawn, which is unique in the world. The Shivalinga here isconsidered Dakshinamukhi, which is rare and special.Mahakaleshwar is located in Ujjain, Madhya Pradesh and is one of the most sacred abodes of Shiva.",
