    english: "<h2> history of Trambakeshwar Jyotirlinga </h2>:--> Trambakeshwar Jyotirlinga is located in the Trambak village, at the source of the Godavari River, in the Nashik district of Maharashtra state. Trambakeshwar is one of the 12 sacred Jyotirlingas of Lord Shiva.According to the Puranas, the sage Gautam Rishi was performing penance in his ashram. Once, during a famine, he performed a yagna to bring rain and water, and worshipped Lord Shiva to bring the Ganges to the earth. Lord Shiva was pleased and brought the Ganges down to this place. This Ganges is known as the Godavari River. Lord Shiva appeared here in his Trinetra (three-eyed) form, known as Trambak, and this form is called Trambakeshwar.It is believed that visiting this sacred place frees devotees from sins and grants them salvation.yambakeshwar is located near Nashik in Maharashtra and is the origin of the Godavari River.",
